To install docker on your computer please follow one of the following installation guides based on your OS:

Windows 10 Pro and Enterprise: https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/install/
May need to enable virtualization via BIOS: https://blogs.technet.microsoft.com/canitpro/2015/09/08/step-by-step-enabling-hyper-v-for-use-on-windows-10/
Windows 10 Home: https://docs.docker.com/toolbox/overview/#ready-to-get-started 
Additional resource: https://docs.docker.com/toolbox/toolbox_install_windows/
May need to enable virtualization via BIOS:
You will have to refer to your laptops manual for the specifics. However, for an HP laptop:
From a fresh start
Hit Esc and F10 keys for BIOS setup
Press the right arrow key and select System Configuration tab, Select Virtualization Technology and press the enter key to enable virtualization
Make sure to save the settings and exit BIOS

Mac OS: https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-mac/install/ 
Ubuntu: https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/#install-from-a-package 
NOTE: Follow the “Install from a package” section only


Verify that docker is installed by opening a shell:

Windows use Power Shell
Mac and Ubuntu use terminal

